modules.description: Provides vector arithmetic operations such as addition, subtraction, dot product, and normalization. Works with 3D floating-point vectors represented as tuples of three floats. Used in physics simulations for force calculations and in graphics pipelines for direction and lighting computations.

This module offers dynamic array operations, including stack-like manipulations (push, pop), element access, and automatic resizing with amortized constant time complexity for insertions. It works with vectors—resizable arrays that manage a user-defined dummy value for unused slots, enabling efficient memory usage. Use cases include implementing stacks with better performance than list-based alternatives and processing sequences requiring frequent growth or transformation.
